<TITLE> Sayedee sued for stealing zakat money </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 24 (bdnews24.com)The Islamic Foundation has sued former Jamaat-e-Islami MP Delwar Hossain Sayedee and former state minister for religion Mosharraf Hossain Shahjahan for embezzling over Tk 10 million in zakat funds. The case details said the duo embezzled the funds of 2004-2005 financial year by allocating the moneys to organisations of their choice. Islamic Foundation's director (finance and accounts) Ayub Ali Chowdhury filed the case with Sher-e-Bangla Nagar Police Station on Monday noon. Officer in charge Md Riaz Hossain told bdnews24.com that the first information report (FIR) stated that the duo along with two others embezzled Tk 12,760,000. Mosharraf was the then state minister for religious affairs and Sayedee was chief of the parliamentary standing committee on religion ministry. Former chairman of the Masjid Council for Community, Maulana Abul Kalam Azad and former finance and account's director Md Lutful Haq were the two others to be charged. bdnews24.
